
        Lifecycle-aware Components Summary:
    1.	Responds to the change in the lifecycle status of other UI components(LifecycleOwner)
    2.	Lifecycle class holds the information about the LifecycleOwner(i.e., Activity)
    3.	Lifecycle object uses enumeration(the action of mentioning a number of things one by one) to track the status:
        •	Event
        •	State
    4.	LifecycleOwner provides lifecycle status to the Lifecycle-aware components.
    5.	LifecycleObserver register the lifecycle status to respond and perform actions.


